## Git Integration for SQL Rules

### Purpose

The SQL Rules are stored in an Azure DevOps Git repository to provide version control, collaborative development and a controlled review process.

This documentation describes the complete workflow from editing a SQL rule to merging the approved changes into the central repository.

---

### Objectives

| Objective       | Benefit                                     |
| --------------- | ------------------------------------------- |
| Version control | Every change is traceable                   |
| Collaboration   | Multiple developers can work simultaneously |
| Code Review     | Higher quality through Pull Requests        |
| Rollback        | Previous versions can easily be restored    |
| Auditability    | Complete change history                     |

